The paper describes a method for reconstructing missing data in datasets, particularly in image and video files. This involves using geometric harmonics to fill in missing values in the dataset. This method is related to machine learning and data analysis, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the use of geometric harmonics suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. The paper may also be relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category, as it involves using algorithms to impute missing data. The use of kernel functions and diagonalization suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Finally, the use of numerical methods suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category.
